The paper proposes a new network embedding method that addresses the limitations of existing methods, such as the lack of generalizability and robustness to noise. The proposed method is evaluated on link prediction tasks, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of graph-based loss, which suggests a potential fit for cs.SD (Software Engineering and Programming) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
